# Week 1 – Day 1
## Topic: GCP Structure

## 1. Objective
What was I trying to understand today?
GCP Hierarchy Organisation---> Folder---> Project---> Resources

## 2. Key Concepts

### Organization
(The Parent Level) The top of the hierarchy, represents your entiere company (e.g Swift Pay) there can only be one organisation 
& it holds everything else inside of it 

### Folder
(The Departments) The second level, its how you owuld section of bsuiness arears ( Engineering finance Marketing)
this can also have sub folders below them to have more persional sections like (Payments, Fruad and Mobile inside engineering) 
alloing you to isolate teams and apply security rules to specific groups

### Project
(The Enviroments) This is where the could work starts to happen and the main billing happens you could seperate your payments team into (payment-prod, Payments-staging ect)
increasing security and containg premissions in smaller niches, if someone accidently delets payment-prod, staging still exists.

### IAM
(identity access managment) a security framework used for access/ premissions for human (principal) or device (Service account), controled by administrators to enable who has access to what resource
Its sort of like giving an employee a card key for an office building that only allows them in specific rooms they need to be in, it also controls what the person can do when they are inside the room 

Who- who or what gets a key card (identity)
What – what the key card can do  (Role)
Were- which “doors” can the key card open  (resource)

Uses the premise of giving people or devices exactly whet they need to conduct their work and no more


